If there's only one image, then just select it and then press 'Open'. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":275,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":455.16483516483515,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
