If there are multiple images, then hold down 'Ctrl' and select as many images as you'll use. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b6/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b6/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":275,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":455.16483516483515,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now click inside the image. If the flashing dashes go around more than you want, using the 'Tool Options', bring the tolerance down. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Collage-in-Arcsoft-Photostudio-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":258,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":425.9340659340659,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

